# Subject: <=72 chars, imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period.
# Example: add OWLv2 detector wrapper

# ---- blank line above separates subject from body ----

# WHAT:  One to three lines. What this commit changes, concretely.
# WHY:   One to three lines. Why the change is needed. Cite the constraint,
#        bug, or decision (ADR-NNNN) that motivated it.
# WHERE: Bullet list of paths touched, with (new) / (mod) / (del) markers.

# Rules (see CONTRIBUTING.md §3):
#   - One logical change per commit.
#   - Docs updated in the same commit as the code they describe.
#   - No "WIP", no "fix stuff", no emoji.
#   - Reference ADRs when implementing one: "Implements ADR-0003."
